    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d473fn1">Sent to the White House Map Room, via military
                        channels, and forwarded by the Map Room to <persName corresp="#p_HC1"
                            >Hull</persName> in paraphrase.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-03">3 December
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and secret from the President.</p>
                <p>I think it best not to appoint International Civil Aviation Committee<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d473fn2">See <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName>’s message of
                        November 29, 1943, to <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_621">p. 621</ref>.</note>
                    until I get back because I think you and I should agree on some general
                    principles to lay before them before they meet.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
